definitions.definition: A tree of the genus Acer , characterised by its usually palmate leaves and winged seeds.
examples: They have a large maple in their yard.

definitions.definition: The wood of such a tree, prized for its hardness and attractive appearance.
examples: This table is made of maple and also has some fruitwood inlays.

definitions.definition: The flavor of such a tree's sap, or an imitation of that flavor.
examples: A: Mmm, this one is strawberry! What flavor is yours? B: This one is maple ! I wonder if any of them will turn out to be pineapple!

main_definition: A tree of the genus Acer , characterised by its usually palmate leaves and winged seeds.
secondary_definitions: The wood of such a tree, prized for its hardness and attractive appearance.
The flavor of such a tree's sap, or an imitation of that flavor.
